title: U.S. cuts military aid to Egypt, sends money instead to Taiwan
description: The Biden administration is withholding an $85 million weapons financing package to Cairo over human rights concerns.

title: Dominican Republic closes border with Haiti, further stoking tensions
description: The neighbors share the Caribbean island of Hispaniola and a long history of strained relations.

title: No significant corruption found in Paris Olympic raid, prosecutor says
description: Three months after raiding Paris 2024 headquarters, France’s top financial prosecutor says no significant corruption has been found in contract rigging investigation.

title: Spanish TV journalist confronts man who she says groped her on live TV
description: Isa Balado was on air when a man appeared to touch her buttocks and the host urged her to “put this idiot on.”

title: Italy’s Meloni campaigned on stopping immigration. It’s not working.
description: Arrivals in Italy have surged to 123,800 so far this year — roughly double last year’s figures, and on track to match or exceed the 2016 record.

title: Norway’s princess Martha Louise sets wedding date to marry American ‘shaman’
description: Norway’s Princess Martha Louise’s relationship with self-described “shaman” Durek Verrett caused a stir after she relinquished royal duties last year.

title: Mexican reporter whom U.S. tried to deport ruled eligible for asylum
description: A Mexican journalist who sought asylum in the United States in 2008 but was arrested in 2017 and told he would be deported, has been declared eligible for asylum.

title: Kim and Putin meeting show just how much the leaders need each other
description: Putin is famous for making world leaders wait, but for North Korea’s Kim Jong Un, he showed up to their meeting early.

title: Libya struggles to deal with thousands of corpses amid fears of disease
description: The lack of early-warning services meant that people were unprepared for Storm Daniel and the toll was much higher, said the World Meteorological Organization.

title: The world hit record temperatures. Then came the deadly floods.
description: The globe’s remarkable warmth — especially of its oceans, most of which have been running several degrees warmer than normal for months — served as a backdrop for all of the floods.

title: 12-year-old became national golf champion after playing only 3 full rounds
description: Bayleigh Teepa-Tarau, a 12-year-old with autism who played with borrowed clubs, won gold at one of New Zealand’s most prestigious youth sporting events.

title: Ukraine live briefing: North Korea’s Kim praises war, will tour Russian aviation factories
description: Kim Jong Un is on his third day in Russia, where he is set to tour military sites. President Vladimir Putin accepted an invitation to visit North Korea.

title: Kim Jong Un’s visit to Russia hints at grim battlefield math for Putin
description: Desperate or determined, Russian President Vladimir Putin is seeking ways to continue the fighting in Ukraine for as long as he can.

title: Stolen Van Gogh piece is returned in a bloody pillowcase inside an Ikea bag
description: One of Van Gogh’s works was stolen in 2020. Three years later, it was returned to Dutch art detective Arthur Brand, dubbed the “Indiana Jones of the art world.”

title: Kim Jong Un in Russia: North Korean leader to tour military sites
description: Kim invited Russia’s Vladimir Putin to make a reciprocal visit to North Korea, after a day of declarations of friendship between the two international outcasts.

title: Self-proclaimed UFO expert shows alleged aliens to Mexico’s Congress
description: Jamie Maussan told lawmakers, under oath, that a 1,000-year-old specimen found in Peru in 2017 is proof of extraterrestrial life. Not everyone was convinced.

title: How a decade of conflict and division put Libya in peril of disaster
description: Conflicts in Libya have left thousands of people dead and the country riven by political turmoil. Those same divisions have exacerbated the flooding disaster.
